A Decaying Study~
Obviously inhabited by someone or something, this chamber is immediately
before a tomb.  Splotches of melted wax can be seen on most everything here.
Wet and smelling strongly of mildew, an old yet fancy carpet covers the cold
granite floor.  An ornate mahogany desk and a matching chair are set up
toward the northern wall, some strange implements and books strewn across
the desk's surface.  One book is opened, though it seems to be in very poor
condition.  A rectangular doorway leads to the west, and an inscription is
visible above it.  
~
