Much of the book is rotted, wet and smeared.  Short passages have somehow
remained legible, despite the poor conditions it has been kept in.  
 
Ah, the horrors of existence... to be given the consciousness to learn,
love and examine the nature of death.  Love, most of all, is both the most
horrid curse and generous gift given to us by our creators.  The thought of
the sweet breath of my dearest Alstea to once more caress my cheek brings me
both ecstacy and agony, for though I look back upon better days, I know that
what comes will never be able to compare.  I have sealed my own fate, it
seems.  Never again will my love's eyes rest in mine, her soft lips part to
smile for me or her hands hold my own.  Alone, I must be, until the end
comes.  Ah, the end... Should she have stolen half of her beauty away with
her to the Fields of Paradise, it would be more than enough to sustain me
for the rest of eternity.
 
The handwriting suddenly becomes much, much worse after this paragraph,
